description.narrative: Satisfactory progress was made despite the challenging situation. UNICEF continued supporting COVID-19 response, with a special focus on COVID-19 vaccine deployment as well as flood response. As of 30th December, 71% of Timorese aged 12 years and above have received the first dose while 57.9 received the second dose.UNICEF also supported the improvement in coverage and quality of routine health services especially expanding cold chain capacity, logistic supports as well as health system strengthening health system. By 30th September 19,771 (83%) children had received 1st dose of Measles-Rubella vaccine. 20,885 (83.2%) deliveries were attended by a qualified health worker. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2021
